value: Resident and intra-African migrant, forest, dense woodland: resident, forest of West Africa - extreme S Sudan and all Ethiopia south to N Angola - S Mozambique; breed visitor north to S Senegal - N Nigeria and into SW Zambia, much of Zimbabwe and NE South Africa (all cupreus); Bioko (intermedius); São Tomé, Príncipe, Pagalu (insularum).
Africa: Senegal and Gambia to South Sudan and Ethiopia, s to Angola and e South Africa
humid forest, riverine forest, savanna, dense bush

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip

value: ground displays, but with occasional jumps/leaps into the air
males and females share resources on their territory only during the breeding season
